messages.content: ROI and Sortino ratios will be 60% of score in this new mechanic, and we believe those are effective metrics to determine real world performance. Initially, the promotion requirement is just a minimum wager and to be 50th percentile miner in the current tier, but in order to rank up consistently into the higher tiers , miners will need to have solid scores across those metrics(relative to other miners). So initially, we may see miners with relatively poor real world performance reach higher tiers, but they will eventually be squeezed out. In order to keep things fair , we need to continue a 1k/day wager without having profit or loss actually impact the miner's "cash" with which to bet. Otherwise it's more likely we end up with some miners becoming entrenched

You could just track their long run performance as a +- on a secondary pool (e.g. miners who make profit on their bets long run pool goes up), and track some variance on that number over time intervals to tier them
Generally in sports betting risk free ratio is set to 0. Balance resets to 1k

Long run performance is essentially just tracked over tiers, so each tier has its own measurement window, up to a 45 day max (which we felt was a decent period for evaluation, though we may eventually extend it further). We don't actually see mean composite score increase much as we move up tiers, its more of a tightening of the std. dev.

We think that CLV + Sortino + ROI gives a fair bit of flexibility for different strategies, and they are normalized so one could be a really good value bettor (consistently positive CLV) and still rank similarly to someone who takes a more "hail mary" type strategy (relying on long-shot odds and good risk management to make a profit even at a ~30% accuracy)

And then as far as outputs, we expect that the top two tiers will have miners which you could copy trade in real world scenarios and be profitable. As it stands right now, we only have about 5 miners that have remained consistently profitable long-term, so we're trying to select for more of those guys (and reward them)

# *V.2.0.0* update is now officially live!

**Bettensor** V.2.0.0 brings you our brand new incentive mechanism. This new mechanism will take us to the next level by introducing a new scoring mechanic and tiered ranking approach.

Incentive Design 2.0 introduces a scoring mechanic that more effectively differentiates miners with effective strategies over a large volume of predictions. We aim to identify the most accurate sports predictors, whose performance would translate well to real-world betting scenarios.

The core framework for the scoring system is a tiered ranking approach, similar to how many video games rank players for online matches. It's designed to keep miners in competition with others of similar skill levels, and provide a progression for truly good sports predictors to earn significant incentives.

The miner score is a composite of several key metrics, including:
- ROI
- Sortino Ratio
- CLV (Closing Line Value)
- Entropy System (Experimental Feature, in Progress) and more.

We hope that by introducing this combination of measures, we can better distribute $TAO incentives in comparison to the value particular miners provide. This novel approach should crystallize professional sports bettors predicting on our subnet and bring overall better predictions that we can share with you; in addition to better data for our ML models!

For a full deep dive into the new incentive mechanism, weighting formula, tier requirements, and score metrics, check out our Substack article here: https://nickel5.substack.com/p/incentive-design-20. 

If you have any further questions or feedback, feel free to send us a message in our Bettensor Discord server: https://discord.gg/SjJWZSEEy8, or SN30 channel on Bittensor's Discord.
